{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-articles-articles-template-js","path":"/articles/vscode/set-up.html","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Happy coding life","author":"@yolokuder"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0596468a-4450-59a0-abe7-a671621f8071","excerpt":"VS Code installation Just jump to VS Code homepage and download VS Code. Then execute the installation. The process is quite straightforward. Some useful VS…","html":"<h1 id=\"vs-code-installation\"><a href=\"#vs-code-installation\" aria-label=\"vs code installation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>VS Code installation</h1>\n<p>Just jump to <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">VS Code homepage</a> and download VS Code.</p>\n<p>Then execute the installation. The process is quite straightforward.</p>\n<h1 id=\"some-useful-vs-code-extensions\"><a href=\"#some-useful-vs-code-extensions\" aria-label=\"some useful vs code extensions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Some useful VS Code extensions</h1>\n<p>To list extrensions has been installed. Just execute the shell</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --list-extensions <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">xargs</span> -L <span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> code --install-extension</code></pre></div>\n<p>To install quickly VS Code extensions as mine. Just execute</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --install-extension dbaeumer.vscode-eslint\ncode --install-extension eamodio.gitlens\ncode --install-extension ecmel.vscode-html-css\ncode --install-extension esbenp.prettier-vscode\ncode --install-extension ms-python.python\ncode --install-extension ms-vscode.csharp\ncode --install-extension msjsdiag.debugger-for-chrome\ncode --install-extension PKief.material-icon-theme\ncode --install-extension wesbos.theme-cobalt2</code></pre></div>\n<p>I will go detail down below section.</p>\n<h1 id=\"cobalt2-theme\"><a href=\"#cobalt2-theme\" aria-label=\"cobalt2 theme permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cobalt2 theme</h1>\n<p>I use <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Cobalt2</code> them and can not be happier with it. The easy way to install <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Cobalt2</code> theme is executinng</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --install-extension wesbos.theme-cobalt2</code></pre></div>\n<p>Do not forget to select <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Cobalt2</code> them for VS code after installing by add to <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">setting.json</code> file</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsxon\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\">{\n  &quot;workbench.colorTheme&quot;: &quot;Cobalt2&quot;\n}</code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"fira-code-font\"><a href=\"#fira-code-font\" aria-label=\"fira code font permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Fira Code Font</h1>\n<p>I use <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Fira Code</code> font for <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">VS Code</code> editor. To install <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Fira Code</code> font, just download <a href=\"https://github.com/tonsky/FiraCode/releases/download/1.206/FiraCode_1.206.zip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Fira Code font</a> and install on your machine.</p>\n<p>I don’t forget to select <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Fira Code</code> font for VS code after installing by adding to <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">setting.json</code> file</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsxon\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\">{\n  &quot;editor.fontFamily&quot;: &quot;Fira Code&quot;,\n  &quot;editor.fontLigatures&quot;: true,\n  &quot;terminal.integrated.fontFamily&quot;: &quot;Fira Code&quot;\n}</code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"material-icon\"><a href=\"#material-icon\" aria-label=\"material icon permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Material icon</h1>\n<p>There is nothing wrong with defaul VS Code icons, but I prefer <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Material style</code> so I install <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Material icon</code> extension for VS code. Just execute the shell</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --install-extension PKief.material-icon-theme</code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"gitlens-for-git\"><a href=\"#gitlens-for-git\" aria-label=\"gitlens for git permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GitLens for Git</h1>\n<p>Working with <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Git</code> should be more joyful, and <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">GitLens</code> bring more experience.</p>\n<p>To install <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">GitLens</code>, just execute the shell</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --install-extension eamodio.gitlens</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now, jump to VS Code and looking at nice features <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Gitlens</code> integrate to code editor, such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Who has change on what</li>\n<li>Time has been changed</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"prettier-for-code-format\"><a href=\"#prettier-for-code-format\" aria-label=\"prettier for code format permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prettier for code format</h1>\n<p>To format code, or even <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Markdown</code>, I use <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Prettier</code> extension. Just execute shell</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --install-extension esbenp.prettier-vscode</code></pre></div>\n<p>I also add more setting to make format automatically. Just add to <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">setting.json</code> file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsxon\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\">{\n  &quot;files.autoSave&quot;: &quot;onFocusChange&quot;,\n  &quot;editor.formatOnSave&quot;: true\n}</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now, whenever I change a file and change focus to other stuffs. <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">VS code</code> will automaically save my document and <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Prettier</code> take responsibility to format the code before saving.</p>\n<h1 id=\"html-css-for-intellisense\"><a href=\"#html-css-for-intellisense\" aria-label=\"html css for intellisense permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Html CSS for intellisense</h1>\n<p>There are nice features to show <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">intellisense</code> when working with <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">CSS</code> using Html CSS extension. Just install by</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --install-extension ecmel.vscode-html-css</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now, when you edit Html file which css class include, you will see intellisense show to your hand.</p>\n<p>I also add some tweak to <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">setting.json</code> file for <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">LESS</code> support.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsxon\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\">{\n  &quot;editor.quickSuggestions&quot;: {\n    &quot;other&quot;: true,\n    &quot;comments&quot;: false,\n    &quot;strings&quot;: true\n  },\n  &quot;css.fileExtensions&quot;: [&quot;css&quot;, &quot;scss&quot;, &quot;less&quot;]\n}</code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"debug-for-chrome\"><a href=\"#debug-for-chrome\" aria-label=\"debug for chrome permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Debug for chrome</h1>\n<p>We are able to use built-in <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Chrome debugger</code>. However, I like to make it happen right in <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">VS Code</code>. Just install <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Debug for Chrome</code> extension. Install by executing</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --install-extension msjsdiag.debugger-for-chrome</code></pre></div>\n<h1 id=\"vs-code-eslint-for-javascript-static-check\"><a href=\"#vs-code-eslint-for-javascript-static-check\" aria-label=\"vs code eslint for javascript static check permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>VS Code ESLint for Javascript static check</h1>\n<p>Every Javascript developer should experience with run time issue and debugging by <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Console.log</code>. However, what if we could catch right away in coding time as the same as working with other strong typing languages such as C# or Java? <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">ESLint</code> would help you a lot. Just install <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">ESLint</code> extension by executing.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-shell\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-shell\">code --install-extension dbaeumer.vscode-eslint</code></pre></div>\n<p>I also make changes to <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">setting.json</code> file which let <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">ESLint</code> do the better job for me. <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">ESLint</code> work well with <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Prettier</code> in smoothly flow. First step is realizing problems using <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">ESLint</code> and then fixing it. After that, send the result of fixing to <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Prettier</code> for formatting the code. This should be done automatically.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsxon\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-jsxon\">{\n  &quot;[javascript]&quot;: {\n    &quot;editor.formatOnSave&quot;: false\n  },\n  &quot;eslint.autoFixOnSave&quot;: true,\n  &quot;eslint.alwaysShowStatus&quot;: true,\n  &quot;prettier.disableLanguages&quot;: [&quot;js&quot;]\n}</code></pre></div>\n<p>Below is my final stuffs:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"./.setting.json\">setting.json</a> file</li>\n<li><a href=\"./.eslintignore\">.eslintignore</a> file</li>\n<li><a href=\"./.eslintrc.js\">.eslintrc.js</a> file</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"VS Code setup","date":"July 07, 2019","description":"Setup VS Code on MAC."}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/articles/vscode/set-up.html"}}}